feat(marketing): Zimbabwean flag + school photos section

Adds a "Built for our schools, with our schools" section with a 4-photo
collage between How-it-works and Pricing, plus a Zimbabwe flag chip in
the hero badge replacing the generic Sparkles icon.

Assets in public/marketing/ (all free for commercial use):
- zimbabwe-flag.svg — Wikimedia Commons, public domain
- classroom-linstedt.jpg — Doug Linstedt, Unsplash License
- students-window-wegener.jpg — bill wegener, Unsplash License
- students-table-montenegro.jpg — Felicia Montenegro, Unsplash License
- uniform-balogun.jpg — Abubakar Balogun, Unsplash License

New component: components/marketing/local-context.tsx
- 6-col x 6-row CSS grid collage (large classroom hero + 2 portrait
  cards stacked + a wide landscape card) on the right
- Copy column on the left grounds the product in local context:
  cash-first workflow, USD pricing, patchy internet tolerance
- Photographer credit + licence note at the foot of the section

Hero badge: replaces lucide Sparkles with next/image of the flag SVG
inside the "Built for Zimbabwean schools" pill.

All images use next/image with proper sizes and aspect-ratio
containers so layout doesn't shift while loading. Total added weight
under 1.2 MB, optimized further by Next on demand.

